
NEWS for SFILE:

## 2021

1.3.1   * fix and clean commands output.
	* Add compile flags.
	* Change line number output and color
	* Rename option -E, --env-path in -w, --which
	* Option -w, --which now print full path for result.

## 2020

1.3.0   * Add long option --ack: like search with default ack program,
          Is just combination to existing options: -lVPrci string_search

1.2.1   * Compil on MacOS.
        * change coding style


## 2011

1.2     * output and bug fixed
	* source cleaned (more speed)
	* add options -Q -u --ign-ext
	* clean output

0.1.11  * source cleaned


0.1.10  * add option --print for print line to find string in file
	* add option --print-all for print all line to find string in file


0.1.9   * add option --exit, for exit program after N result found
	* add flags for the compile : -Wall


0.1.8   * delete test.sh
	* add option ---put-inode for print inode file
	* add option --color for colorize output
	* add option --ign-archive for ignore archive (.tar,zip etc)
	* sfile is portable for *BSD (tested on FreeBSD 8)


### 2010

0.1.2	* add option --env-path, for search in directory that in variable of environement PATH
	* add option --no-scan for ignore object if word in name, and if object is directory,
	  and recursive mode ON, y not scanned after
	* add option --extension (-e) for search file with special extension
	* add --infos for display file informations (perm, size, user)

	
0.1.1	* add option ignore file or directory (--file-ign or --dir-ign)
	* add option "--full-path", if you not specified a path, research current path,
	  and  if option full-path ok, print full path, else current path replaced by "./"
	* bug-fixed, sometimes one directory not listed

0.1.0   * First version
